{"add":{"doc":{"id":"33a486bad0ba8159214e7b48bc131b51314e960c8b509ebaa29831c365c0edd9","url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f0/Railfone.jpg/220px-Railfone.jpg","previous":[],"after":["An increasing number of countries, particularly in Europe, now have more mobile phones than people. According to the figures from Eurostat, the European Union's in-house statistical office, Luxembourg had the highest mobile phone penetration rate at 158 mobile subscriptions per 100 people, closely followed by Lithuania and Italy.[15] In Hong Kong the penetration rate reached 139.8% of the population in July 2007.[16] Over 50 countries have mobile phone subscription penetration rates higher than that of the population and the Western European average penetration rate was 110% in 2007 (source Informa 2007). Canada currently has the lowest rates of mobile phone penetrations in the industrialised world at 58%."]}}}